::Fidgit::

She walked around the arc.  She heard noises but didn't care.  She was tired 
of not getting any assignments to do.  She walked outside the arc and went 
to the lake.  She swam in the cool water and played with the fish.  she 
loved just being able to swim freely and feel the water glide over her body 
effortlessly.  She felt like she could fly when she swam.  Her head broke 
the surface of the water and she looked about.
"Hmm, no one about. This is good." She dove back under water and went down 
into the depths.  She went up for air and went back down again.  She looked 
around and saw some trees that had fallen into the water and climbed over 
then.  She found a tunnel.  Where it went to she didn't know.  She decided 
to wait before going in and exploring the tunnel. She wanted to make sure it 
was safe so she sat on the shore bank and waited for a few moments.  If no 
one came, then she would dive back down and explore the cave.
